description: Manchester City Football Club is an English football club from Manchester, founded in 1880 as West Gorton Saint Marks. In 1887 the name was changed to Ardwick Football Club and in 1894 it adopted its current name. The club plays its home games at the Etihad Stadium, in East Manchester. It won the UEFA Champions League for the first time in club history in 2023. The UEFA Super Cup and FIFA Club World Cup were also won that season, making the international treble a reality.

Real Madrid Club de Fútbol is a Spanish football club from Madrid. The club was founded on March 6, 1902 as Madrid Club de Fútbol. Usually the current club name is abbreviated to Real Madrid. In addition, it has some nicknames, such as Los Blancos and Los Merengues. The club plays its home games at the Estadio Santiago Bernabéu and was named by FIFA as the best football club of the 20th century.[1] Real Madrid's arch rival is FC Barcelona, ​​matches between both clubs are known as El Clásico. Real Madrid have won the Primera División thirty-five times, the Copa del Rey twenty times, the Supercopa de España thirteen times, the UEFA Super Cup five times, the UEFA Cup twice, the Intercontinental Cup three times, the FIFA Club World Cup five times and fourteen times the European Cup I / UEFA Champions League. Real Madrid is the record holder of the tournament with fourteen European Cup I / UEFA Champions League victories, ahead of the Italian AC Milan, which won the tournament seven times.

Juventus Football Club is one of the oldest football clubs in Italy. The club plays its home games at the Allianz Stadium in Turin. Juventus was one of the few top European clubs to win all three UEFA main competitions (European Cup I / UEFA Champions League, European Cup II and UEFA Cup / UEFA Europa League), together with Manchester United, Ajax, Chelsea and Bayern Munich. Juventus is Latin for youth.

Fußball-Club Bayern Munich, simply FC Bayern Munich, Bayern Munich or FC Bayern, is a German football club from Munich, which plays in the Bundesliga and was founded in 1900. Its home stadium was the Grünwalder Stadion from 1925 to 1972, and the Grünwalder Stadion from 1925 to 1972. Stadium until the summer of 2005. Olympiastadion and since then the Allianz Arena. FC Bayern Munich is the best-known and most successful club in Germany and belongs to the European and world top. FC Bayern was one of the few top European clubs to win all three UEFA main competitions (European Cup I / UEFA Champions League, European Cup II and UEFA Cup / UEFA Europa) together with Manchester United FC, AFC Ajax, Juventus FC and Chelsea. . League) to win. It is striking that the rise of this association, which until around 1965 was smaller than city rival TSV 1860 Munich, coincided with the rise of Franz Beckenbauer.

Paris Saint-Germain Football Club commonly referred to as PSG or Paris Saint Germain is a French football club based in the capital Paris. Founded in 1970 as a merger club, it rose to prominence in 2011 through the takeover by Qatar Sports Investments. It is the most successful club in France with forty-six national and international titles and has been playing at the highest level continuously since 1974, longer than any other club in the French league. PSG's traditional equipment consists of a blue and red kit. The club's stadium is Parc des Princes. Paris Saint-Germain won a record eleven league titles. PSG's arch rival is Olympique Marseille, the matches between both clubs are known as Le Classique.

Amsterdamsche Football Club Ajax, AFC Ajax or simply Ajax, is a Dutch professional football club from Amsterdam. The club was founded on March 18, 1900 and is one of the three traditional top clubs in the Netherlands. Since the founding of the Eredivisie, Ajax has continuously played in this top division. Ajax became Dutch champions thirty-six times, twenty-eight of which since the introduction of the Eredivisie in mid-1956.

Sport Lisboa e Benfica, simply Benfica, is a Portuguese football club from Lisbon. Benfica is a neighborhood in Lisbon. SL Benfica was founded in 1904 as Sport Lisboa, but was renamed in 1908 after a merger with Sport Club de Benfica. Benfica plays its home games at the Estádio da Luz. The club's mascot is an eagle, which flies over the field at home games and lands on the center spot. Hence the members of the club are nicknamed as aguias, 'the eagles'.

Royal Sporting Club Anderlecht is a Belgian football club from Brussels, more specifically from the Brussels municipality of Anderlecht. The club was founded on May 27, 1908 and is affiliated with the Football Association with registration number 35.The team has purple and white as club colors and plays its home games in the Lotto Park where there is room for 22.500 spectators. RSC Anderlecht has played continuously in the First Division since 1935 and has since won the national title thirty-four times, the Belgian Cup nine times and the Belgian Super Cup ten times.

Fenerbahçe Spor Kulübü is a sports club founded in 1907 in Fenerbahçe, a district in the city of Istanbul. The club colors are yellow and navy blue. The home ground of the football club is the Şükrü Saracoğlu Stadium. Since its founding, the club has been active in 35 different sports. Fenerbahçe profiles itself in Europe mainly with its football team. The club is considered one of the largest and most popular clubs in Turkey. Fenerbahçe SK has nine active sports: basketball, volleyball, rowing, boxing, sailing, athletics, swimming and table tennis. The football team is active in the highest Turkish football division. The men's and women's basketball team and the men's and women's volleyball team also play in the highest Turkish divisions. The football team's highest position in the IFFHS world rankings is 15th. The club has a number of rivals in Turkey such as Trabzonspor and Beşiktaş. The biggest rival is fellow city Galatasaray.

The Celtic Football Club is a football club from Glasgow in Scotland, founded in 1887. The club plays its home games at Celtic Park, which seats 60,411 spectators. The club colors are green-white. Celtic play a leading role in the Scottish football competition and provide many international players for the national team. Celtic have a long, fierce rivalry with Rangers FC, who are considered their arch-rivals. The matches between both clubs are known as The Old Firm. The battle for the national championship is often between Celtic and Rangers, usually with a big lead over the other clubs. Aberdeen was the last club to break this hegemony, in the 1984/85 season.
